    • Constructor Detail

      • GroupByPlan

        public GroupByPlan(Plan p,
                   Set<String> groupFlds,
                   Set<AggregationFn> aggFns,
                   Transaction tx)
        Creates a group-by plan for the underlying query. The grouping is determined by the specified collection of group fields, and the aggregation is computed by the specified collection of aggregation functions.
        Parameters:
        p - a plan for the underlying query
        groupFlds - the fields to group by. Can be empty, which means that all records are in a single group.
        aggFns - the aggregation functions. Optional, can be null.
        tx - the calling transaction

    • Method Detail

      • groupByHistogram

        public static Histogram groupByHistogram(Histogram hist,
                                         Set<String> groupFlds,
                                         Set<AggregationFn> aggFns)
        Returns a histogram that, for each field, approximates distribution of values in the group-by and aggregation fields.

        Assumes that:

        • Distributions of values in group-by fields are independent with each other
        • Aggregate values in different groups are distinct
        Parameters:
        hist - the input join distribution of field values
        groupFlds - the fields to group by. Can be empty, which means that all records are in a single group.
        aggFns - the aggregation functions. Optional, can be null.
        Returns:
        a histogram that, for each field, approximates distribution of values in the group-by and aggregation fields

        public long blocksAccessed()
